<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p id="Par61">A DNA sequence can be numerically characterised by a 3
 <italic>K</italic> dimension vector 
 <italic>V</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>tp</italic>
 </sub>:
 <disp-formula id="Equt">
  <alternatives>
   <tex-math id="M51">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} $$ {\displaystyle \begin{array}{c}{V}_{\mathrm{tp}}=\left({x}_1-{x}_0,{x}_2-{x}_1,\dots, {x}_k-{x}_{k-1},\right.\\ {}{y}_1-{y}_0,{y}_2-{y}_1,\dots, {y}_k-{y}_{k-1},\\ {}\left.{z}_1-{z}_0,{z}_2-{z}_1,\dots, {z}_k-{z}_{k-1}\right)\end{array}} $$ \end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M52" display="block">
    <mtable displaystyle="true" groupalign="right left">
     <mtr>
      <mtd>
       <msub>
        <mi>V</mi>
        <mi>tp</mi>
       </msub>
       <maligngroup/>
       <mo>=</mo>
       <mfenced close="" open="(" separators=",,,,">
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mn>1</mn>
         </msub>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mn>0</mn>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mn>2</mn>
         </msub>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mn>1</mn>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
        <mo>…</mo>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mi>k</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow>
           <mi>k</mi>
           <mo>−</mo>
           <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
        <mrow/>
       </mfenced>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
     <mtr>
      <mtd>
       <maligngroup/>
       <msub>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </msub>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mn>0</mn>
       </msub>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mn>2</mn>
       </msub>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </msub>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mo>…</mo>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mi>k</mi>
       </msub>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mi>k</mi>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo>,</mo>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
     <mtr>
      <mtd>
       <maligngroup/>
       <mfenced close=")" open="" separators=",,,">
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>z</mi>
          <mn>1</mn>
         </msub>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>z</mi>
          <mn>0</mn>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>z</mi>
          <mn>2</mn>
         </msub>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>z</mi>
          <mn>1</mn>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
        <mo>…</mo>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>z</mi>
          <mi>k</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>z</mi>
          <mrow>
           <mi>k</mi>
           <mo>−</mo>
           <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
       </mfenced>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
    </mtable>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="453959_1_En_9_Chapter_Equt.gif" position="anchor" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>which in the case of our sample sequence will be:
 <disp-formula id="Equu">
  <alternatives>
   <tex-math id="M53">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} $$ {\displaystyle \begin{array}{c}{V}_{\mathrm{tp}}=\left(0,1,0.5774,0,0,0,-1,-1,\right.\\ {}\kern0.62em 0,0,0.5774,0,0,0,0,0,\\ {}\left.-1,0,0.5774,1,1,1,0,0\right)\end{array}} $$ \end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M54" display="block">
    <mtable displaystyle="true" groupalign="right left">
     <mtr>
      <mtd>
       <msub>
        <mi>V</mi>
        <mi>tp</mi>
       </msub>
       <maligngroup/>
       <mo>=</mo>
       <mfenced close="" open="(" separators=",,,,,,,,">
        <mn>0</mn>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mn>0.5774</mn>
        <mn>0</mn>
        <mn>0</mn>
        <mn>0</mn>
        <mrow>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mrow/>
       </mfenced>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
     <mtr>
      <mtd>
       <maligngroup/>
       <mspace width="0.62em"/>
       <mn>0</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mn>0</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mn>0.5774</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mn>0</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mn>0</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mn>0</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mn>0</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mn>0</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
     <mtr>
      <mtd>
       <maligngroup/>
       <mfenced close=")" open="" separators=",,,,,,,">
        <mrow>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mn>0</mn>
        <mn>0.5774</mn>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mn>0</mn>
        <mn>0</mn>
       </mfenced>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
    </mtable>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="453959_1_En_9_Chapter_Equu.gif" position="anchor" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>Now, for any two sequences 
 <italic>S</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>a</italic>
 </sub>
 <italic>, S</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>b</italic>
 </sub>, if their descriptor values are 
 <italic>a</italic> = (
 <italic>a</italic>
 <sub>1</sub>, 
 <italic>a</italic>
 <sub>2</sub>, …, 
 <italic>a</italic>
 <sub>3
  <italic>K</italic>
 </sub>) and 
 <italic>b</italic> = (
 <italic>b</italic>
 <sub>1</sub>, 
 <italic>b</italic>
 <sub>2</sub>, …, 
 <italic>b</italic>
 <sub>3
  <italic>K</italic>
 </sub>),respectively, their similarity can be calculated by the Euclidean distance given by:
 <disp-formula id="Equv">
  <alternatives>
   <tex-math id="M55">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} $$ d\left(a,b\right)=\sqrt{\sum \limits_{j=1}^{3k}{\left({a}_j-{b}_j\right)}^2} $$ \end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M56" display="block">
    <mi>d</mi>
    <mfenced close=")" open="(" separators=",">
     <mi>a</mi>
     <mi>b</mi>
    </mfenced>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <msqrt>
     <mrow>
      <munderover>
       <mo>∑</mo>
       <mrow>
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </mrow>
       <mrow>
        <mn>3</mn>
        <mi>k</mi>
       </mrow>
      </munderover>
      <msup>
       <mfenced close=")" open="(">
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mi>j</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>b</mi>
          <mi>j</mi>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
       </mfenced>
       <mn>2</mn>
      </msup>
     </mrow>
    </msqrt>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="453959_1_En_9_Chapter_Equv.gif" position="anchor" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>whereby, the smaller the 
 <italic>d</italic>(
 <italic>a</italic>, 
 <italic>b</italic>), the more similar are the two DNA sequences.
</p>
